OL,3,CWhat's first on Andy Burnham's agenda
OL,4,Cas prime minister?
OL,6,FOn the steps of Downing Street on
OL,7,FMonday, Burnham vowed that his first
OL,8,Fact as prime minister would be to
OL,9,Finstruct plans to end rough sleeping,
OL,10,Finvesting #340 million into the idea.
OL,12,FThis comes on top of the previous
OL,13,Fgovernment's allocation of #3.5
OL,14,Fbillion for the National Plan to End
OL,15,FHomelessness, which was designed to
OL,16,Fhalf the rates of long-term rough
OL,17,Fsleeping.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1784702922
OL,3,CWhat's first on Andy Burnham's agenda
OL,4,Cas prime minister?
OL,6,FThis follows his previous "A Bed Every
OL,7,FNight" programme in Manchester, which
OL,8,Fhe pledged to donate 15% of his
OL,9,Fmayoral salary to and saw rough
OL,10,Fsleeping drop by two thirds in his
OL,11,Ffirst five years as mayor.
OL,13,FSome critics point to the continued
OL,14,Frise in homelessness in Greater
OL,15,FManchester over the past four years
OL,16,Fbut Burnham claimed a lack of a joined
OL,17,Fup approach by other authorities meant
OL,18,Fpeople came to the area to seek
OL,19,Fsupport.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1784702922
OL,3,CWhat's first on Andy Burnham's agenda
OL,4,Cas prime minister?
OL,6,FFurther details set out by No 10 said
OL,7,Fthe additional funding would go
OL,8,Ftowards acquiring suitable homes,
OL,9,Fidentifying those most in need and
OL,10,Fstarting to provide housing and
OL,11,Fsupport "without delay".
OL,13,FThe government claimed that this
OL,14,Ffunding uplift will provide 1,200
OL,15,Fhomes and intensive support for at
OL,16,Fleast 3,000 long-term rough sleepers
OL,17,Fover a five year period.
OL,26,@sD@IOUsD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
